.TH lis_solver_set_option 3 "14 Sep 2017" "Man Page" "Lis Library Functions"

.SH NAME

lis_solver_set_option \- set the options for the solver

.SH SYNOPSIS

#include "lis.h"

\fBLIS_INT lis_solver_set_option\fR(\fBchar *text\fR, \fBLIS_SOLVER *solver\fR);

.SH DESCRIPTION

Set the options for the solver.

.SH INPUT

.IP "\fBtext\fR"
The command line options

.SH OUTPUT

.IP "\fBsolver\fR"
The solver

.SH EXIT STATUS

The following exit values are returned:
.IP "0"
The process is normally terminated
.IP "unspecified"
An error occurred

.SH NOTE

The table below shows the available command line options, where -i {\fIcg\fR|1} means -i \fIcg\fR 
or -i 1 and -maxiter [1000] indicates that -maxiter defaults to 1,000.

